<subSubSection pageId="419" pageNumber="420" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="419" pageNumber="420">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="419" pageNumber="420">
The range of this species extends from the Aleutian Islands and the Gulf of Alaska coast to southwestern Yukon Territory (Lindroth 1963b: 273, as 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="419" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incertum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="419" pageNumber="420">Bembidion incertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), south to north-central New Mexico (Fall and Cockerell 1907: 157; Hayward 1897: 68, as 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="419" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incertum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="419" pageNumber="420">Bembidion incertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) along the Rocky Mountains and to the Sierra Nevada in eastern California (Casey 1918: 30, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="419" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="419" pageNumber="420">Bembidion testatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
